@baseUrl = http://localhost:3001

### Health check
GET {{baseUrl}}/health

### Dashboard stats — counts by status/priority + breached/at-risk
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/dashboard/stats

### List agents (for the assign dropdown)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/agents

### List tickets (default pagination)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/tickets

### List tickets — filter by status + priority
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/tickets?status=open&priority=urgent

### List tickets — subject search
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/tickets?search=login

### List tickets — pagination
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/tickets?page=1&limit=5

### Get one ticket with comments + SLA events
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/tickets/1

### Create a ticket (201)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/tickets
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "subject": "New ticket from api.http",
  "description": "Testing the create endpoint",
  "priority": "urgent"
}

### Create — validation error (422, invalid priority)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/tickets
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "subject": "bad ticket",
  "priority": "nope"
}

### Create — validation error (422, missing subject)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/tickets
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "priority": "low"
}

### Change status — valid transition (open -> in_progress)
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/api/tickets/1/status
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "status": "in_progress"
}

### Change status — invalid transition (closed -> in_progress) 422
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/api/tickets/11/status
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "status": "in_progress"
}

### Assign an agent
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/api/tickets/1/assign
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "agent_id": 2
}

### Assign — non-existent agent (404)
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/api/tickets/1/assign
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "agent_id": 9999
}

### Add a comment (201)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/tickets/1/comments
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "author": "customer",
  "message": "Any update on this?"
}

### Get a non-existent ticket (404)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/tickets/99999
